# HTML and other non-fingerprinted assets: a short cache so content edits
# propagate quickly. Cloudflare _headers MERGES same-name headers from every
# matching rule (it is not most-specific-wins), so the fingerprinted /fonts/*
# rule below first strips this inherited value with `! Cache-Control`; otherwise
# those assets would get a combined "max-age=600, …, immutable" header and
# browsers would honor the 600, defeating the long cache.
/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=600
# Fingerprinted assets carry a content hash in their filename, so they can be
# cached forever — a content change yields a new URL. (The CSS is inlined into
# the HTML, so the only fingerprinted assets left are the fonts.)
/fonts/*
  ! Cache-Control
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
# Serve the install script as plain text so it's inspectable before piping to sh.
/gitcalver.sh
  Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8
